 cloud by freshly\naccelerated CRs escaped from an isolated SNR at the end of the Sedov-Taylor\nphase. The second model naturally provides an explanation for the injection of\nother short-lived radionuclides of stellar origin into the cold presolar\nmolecular cloud ($^{26}$Al, $^{41}$Ca and $^{36}$Cl) and is in agreement with\nthe solar system originating from the collapse of a molecular cloud shocked by\na supernova blast wave.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Oct 2014 16:55:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
